WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:13.935 --> 00:00:15.060
MALE SPEAKER: Good morning.

00:00:15.060 --> 00:00:18.670
Welcome to Authors
at Google Cambridge.

00:00:18.670 --> 00:00:20.890
And welcome to Pride Week.

00:00:20.890 --> 00:00:24.970
It's my enormous pleasure
to kick off Pride Week here

00:00:24.970 --> 00:00:30.870
in Cambridge by introducing four
exceptionally talented writers.

00:00:30.870 --> 00:00:33.590
They happen to be trans women.

00:00:33.590 --> 00:00:38.790
They are part of the growing
group of Topside Press writers

00:00:38.790 --> 00:00:44.000
who are giving voice to
people whose voices have long

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:47.400
since been denied in
the publishing world

00:00:47.400 --> 00:00:52.950
and who are changing lives
even as we stand here.

00:00:52.950 --> 00:00:57.900
Today, we have four writers who
are part of the Topside Press

00:00:57.900 --> 00:01:00.670
Northeastern Tour.

00:01:00.670 --> 00:01:04.560
Two writers will be
back in Cambridge a week

00:01:04.560 --> 00:01:09.795
from tomorrow, the 17th, at a
location whose name I forget,

00:01:09.795 --> 00:01:14.320
but who Red Durkin can
probably remind us of.

00:01:14.320 --> 00:01:18.430
But this morning, we welcome
Imogen Binnie, Red Durkin,

00:01:18.430 --> 00:01:22.040
Casey Plett, and
Jeanne Thornton.

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:25.235
Imogen Binnie writes a
monthly column in "Maximum

00:01:25.235 --> 00:01:29.320
Rock'n'Roll" magazine as well
as the zines "The Fact That

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:34.160
It's Funny Doesn't Make It A
Joke" and "Stereotype Threat."

00:01:34.160 --> 00:01:36.520
She was a contributor
to the Topside Press

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:40.240
"The Collection-- Short Fiction
from the Transgender Vanguard,"

00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:42.620
which I highly recommend.

00:01:42.620 --> 00:01:46.430
She was recently named a
recipient of the 2014 Betty

00:01:46.430 --> 00:01:49.950
Burzon Emerging Writer Award.

00:01:49.950 --> 00:01:52.000
Also, her novel
"Nevada," which is

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:55.140
available in the back of
the room after the talk,

00:01:55.140 --> 00:01:58.920
has been the recent subject
of not one, not two,

00:01:58.920 --> 00:02:03.430
but three video games
produced at one of our most

00:02:03.430 --> 00:02:06.490
prestigious engineering
universities,

00:02:06.490 --> 00:02:11.110
Georgia Tech University,
alongside another classic

00:02:11.110 --> 00:02:15.530
of the genre, James
Baldwin's "Giovanni's Room."

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:17.660
So there you have it.

00:02:17.660 --> 00:02:21.830
If you never thought you
would see a video game based

00:02:21.830 --> 00:02:27.830
on "Giovanni's Room"-- I
never did-- we're both wrong.

00:02:27.830 --> 00:02:32.650
Red Durkin is, for
obscure reasons,

00:02:32.650 --> 00:02:36.660
sadly by default, the prettiest
and funniest stand-up comedian

00:02:36.660 --> 00:02:37.960
in New York City now.

00:02:41.050 --> 00:02:43.550
RED DURKIN: According to
the comedian reporter.

00:02:43.550 --> 00:02:45.762
FEMALE SPEAKER: Oh, yeah.

00:02:45.762 --> 00:02:48.040
MALE SPEAKER: She's also
a very talented writer

00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:51.530
and a dogged activist.

00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:54.941
She is the managing
editor of PrettyQueer.com.

00:02:54.941 --> 00:02:57.090
She has written
nine zines and was

00:02:57.090 --> 00:03:00.635
featured in the final issue
of Punk Planet magazine

00:03:00.635 --> 00:03:04.290
and contributed to
"The Collection."

00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:06.590
Casey Plett has just
published a collection

00:03:06.590 --> 00:03:09.270
of stories, "A
Safe Girl to Love,"

00:03:09.270 --> 00:03:13.950
the dedication of which is
particularly near to my heart.

00:03:13.950 --> 00:03:16.640
Previously, she wrote a
column on transitioning

00:03:16.640 --> 00:03:19.330
for McSweeney's
Internet Tendency

00:03:19.330 --> 00:03:23.350
and contributed to
"The Collection."

00:03:23.350 --> 00:03:24.850
And Jeanne Thornton
is the author

00:03:24.850 --> 00:03:28.600
of "The Black Emerald," which
is forthcoming later this year,

00:03:28.600 --> 00:03:30.640
and "The Dream of
Doctor Bantam,"

00:03:30.640 --> 00:03:34.840
which was a Lambda
Award finalist for 2012,

00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:37.630
as well as the web comics
"Bad Mother" and "The Man

00:03:37.630 --> 00:03:39.230
Who Hates Fun."

00:03:39.230 --> 00:03:42.200
Please join me in welcoming
these four very talented

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:43.702
writers.

